And he's also chairman of the Anthropology Department.

06:53.980 --> 07:00.400
Actually I was chairman of the Department of Anthropology from 1967 to 1971.

07:01.840 --> 07:06.880
And when I resigned, I swore I would never do it again under any circumstances whatsoever.

07:07.680 --> 07:12.880
And so here I am in the third year of my second chairmanship.

07:13.520 --> 07:15.900
And I figure I've got one year to go.

07:16.820 --> 07:19.900
And then somebody else is going to take over.

07:20.740 --> 07:25.680
And hopefully I can get back to writing not on a full time basis, but I can sure write

07:25.680 --> 07:28.140
more than I can when I'm tied up with the chairmanship.

07:28.340 --> 07:29.580
It's really a full time job.

07:30.580 --> 07:34.820
With a distinguished career at the University, Oliver still spends time writing science fiction.

07:35.060 --> 07:36.540
We have to buy for the money.

07:37.180 --> 07:42.660
No, I really think that writing is something you have to do.

07:43.880 --> 07:47.920
And at any rate, that's the way it is with me.

07:48.080 --> 07:54.660
When I go a certain length of time without writing anything or trying to write something,

07:54.900 --> 07:58.420
I get actually physically uncomfortable with it.

07:58.680 --> 08:01.360
And it's definitely a labor of love.

08:01.360 --> 08:06.340
I think of myself as an anthropologist who occasionally writes a story.

08:07.060 --> 08:11.000
I think that the way to be forever is I really live.

08:11.900 --> 08:18.320
What I am is a writer who got interested in anthropology rather than the other way around.

08:19.020 --> 08:22.000
And it means more to me, I think.

08:22.180 --> 08:24.560
It's more gratifying than anything else.

08:25.660 --> 08:27.140
I just pulled a story.

08:28.340 --> 08:31.500
It's an analog, a story called Ghost Town.

08:31.840 --> 08:35.960
It's going to be out in either September or October, if you will.

08:36.680 --> 08:45.100
And I was thrilled when analog, and it's almost like I'd never told a story before.

08:45.720 --> 08:50.280
And it's infinitely important from the other things when I did.

08:50.280 --> 08:51.000
It's an analog.

08:58.240 --> 09:01.340
Oliver is recognized for his use of anthropology in science fiction,

09:01.680 --> 09:03.800
and it's probably the first science fiction author to do so.

09:04.160 --> 09:08.200
He's even had one of his novels, Shadows in the Sun, reviewed in the anthropology journal.

09:08.540 --> 09:11.360
We estimate the use of anthropology as deliberate.

09:12.560 --> 09:13.800
It's a sound like sound.

09:14.360 --> 09:18.100
But it was certainly nothing that I'd set down and planned.

09:18.660 --> 09:23.540
Like, here's an effective way to teach anthropology that I'm going to do with a three-science fiction.

09:25.000 --> 09:32.020
I really think that the actual proof of the situation is that any writer writes about other things that they know.

09:32.960 --> 09:35.180
And one of the things that I knew was anthropology.

09:35.920 --> 09:37.260
So it's more or less natural.

09:37.760 --> 09:40.680
A fair amount of my writing is rooted in anthropology.

09:41.460 --> 09:43.220
But by no means all of it.

09:43.220 --> 09:49.060
And it's particularly important in the short of the stories that I like the most.

09:49.240 --> 09:51.100
I don't know what anybody else might like about it.

09:51.740 --> 09:55.160
It's kind of a story that you don't have anything to do with anthropology at all.

09:55.840 --> 09:58.520
Although, you know, I don't even go on about this.

09:59.120 --> 10:00.960
I'm just about to rally on.

10:01.740 --> 10:08.700
But at the point of the influence that you can frequently ask much at the same time,

10:08.700 --> 10:09.480
and I'm just going to start with a question.

10:10.440 --> 10:12.660
Among them, what does it mean to be human?

10:13.300 --> 10:15.220
Where are we going and where are we going?

10:16.320 --> 10:24.520
And it seems to me that if you're involved seriously in the field, you tend to fall into the other one.

10:25.500 --> 10:30.040
I would guess, I don't know whether anybody's ever actually counted enough.

10:30.740 --> 10:37.540
But I suppose something like 50% of my writing, perhaps, is rooted directly in anthropology.

10:37.540 --> 10:39.440
But there's a sense that it isn't.

